  "text": "(1) Leaf resistance to fracture. For measuring the average force needed to fracture a leaf at a constant shearing angle of 20° and speed, [CITATION_1] described and illustrated an apparatus, a calibrated copy of which is available for use at CNRS in Montpellier, France (contact Eric Garnier, email garnier@cefe.cnrs-mop.fr). Leaves are cut at right angles to the midrib, at the widest point along the lamina (or halfway between base and tip if this is difficult to determine).",
